Beginning on Monday, April 20, Thomasville High School will transition from "Remote" Learning to "E-Learning." Instruction may include live or recorded audio or video instruction, one-to-one conferencing, large group instruction, small group collaboration, etc. via various platforms like Canvas, Google Classroom, Zoom, and so on. Teahcers will establish regular office hours where they will be available online to deliver lessons and answer any questions students may have.

Click this link for more information - https://ths.tcs.k12.nc.us/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=1696019&type=d&pREC_ID=1856705

TCS employees should plan on a workday on Monday, March 16.

Greeting Thomasville High Parents and Community,

In our efforts to make THS the best school for our students and community, we have posted a brief online survey on our webpage.
Please go to our page under latest news at: http://ths.tcs.k12.nc.us/ and take the survey so we can best continue to meet the needs of our families and students.
Thank you for providing us with your valuable feedback and have a great bulldog evening.
